Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @spring onions{2} then slice thinly. Halve and thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}.

Pop the radish in a small #bowl{} and add the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and the @sugar{1}. Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!). Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the pan to a bowl and set aside for later.

> Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Pop your frying pan back on medium high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once hot, add the red onion and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and peppers, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and stir fry until softened too, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{300%g} to the pan, break them apart gently with your hands first, and stir fry, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{75%ml} along with a splash of @water{1%splash}. Stir through to combine and cook until everything is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide equally into #bowls{} and top with the pickled radish, spring onion and toasted sesame seeds. Enjoy!